    "answer_id" : 32880383,
    "question_id" : 3144940,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>image_view.getLayoutParams().height \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>returns height value in pixels. You need to get the screen dimensions first to set the values properly.</p>\n\n<pre><code> Display display = context.getWindowManager().getDefaultDisplay();\n DisplayMetrics outMetrics = new DisplayMetrics();\n display.getMetrics(outMetrics);\n int screen_height = outMetrics.heightPixels;\n int screen_width = outMetrics.widthPixels;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>After you get the screen dimensions, you can set the imageview width&amp;height using proper margins.</p>\n\n<pre><code> view.getLayoutParams().height = screen_height - 140;\n view.getLayoutParams().width = screen_width - 130 ;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6622474,
      "reputation" : 3617,
      "user_id" : 5113666,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 11,
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Yd2-yh3cJKU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAFE/TENxYyAbRMM/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Ali Kahoot",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5113666/ali-kahoot"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1449393762,
    "creation_date" : 1449393762,
    "answer_id" : 34115858,
    "question_id" : 3144940,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The best and easiest way to set a button dynamically is </p>\n\n<pre><code> Button index=new Button(this);\n int height = (int) TypedValue.applyDimension(TypedValue.COMPLEX_UNIT_DIP, 45, getResources().getDisplayMetrics());             \n int width = (int) TypedValue.applyDimension(TypedValue.COMPLEX_UNIT_DIP, 42, getResources().getDisplayMetrics());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The above height and width are in pixels <strong>px</strong>. 45 being the height in <strong>dp</strong> and 42 being the width in <strong>dp</strong>.</p>\n\n<pre><code> index.setLayoutParams(new &lt;Parent&gt;.LayoutParams(width, height));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>So, for example, if you've placed your button within a TableRow within a TableLayout, you should have it as TableRow.LayoutParams</p>\n\n<pre><code> index.setLayoutParams(new TableRow.LayoutParams(width, height));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1161685,
      "reputation" : 16651,
      "user_id" : 1141063,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 60,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/s5hsK.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Omar",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1141063/omar"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
